c. 7 km past Harrar,along the road to Jijiga.

7km past Misughaa on Mwa Mtoro rd. Rolling hills, midslope, gray silty soil. Miombo woodland 8-10(-20)m dominated by Brachystegia spiciformis, also open woody layer at 3-6m with Terminalia, Combretum, Commiphora africana.

T6. Mindu Forest Reserve, ca. 200 m N of main road to Mikumi N of Mindu Lake. Rocky thicket woodland dominated by Dichrostachys cinerea, Diplorhynchus condylocarpon, Pseudolachnostylis maprouneifolia, Acacia nigrescens, Dalbergia melanoxylon, Afzelia quanzensis, Julbernardia globiflora, Tamarindus indica, Steganotaenia araliacea, Pteleopsis sp., Brachystegia boehmii, Balanites aegyptiaca, Kigelia africana, Xerophyta spekei, Ximenia americana and Ficus sp.
(T1) Nyigogo Ward, Kipeja Village. Permanent swamp edges and in water.

Ngorongoro Conservation Area Endulen Hospital, 2 km North of Endulen Village. Shrub savanna. Information given by Saning'o ole Nakuroi, Iltareto-age-group, ca. 85 years and Lepilal ole Nakuroi, Irking'onde-agegroup, c. 30 year.
Serengeti National Park. 3 km NW of Banagi on Ikoma road.
Central Prov., Thika Dist., along Thika Road, 6.5 mi. N.E. of Ruiru.
Rock valley, between Dacata R. and Babile on the Harar-Jijiga road.
